# Fire Vantage environment variables. Copy to .env for local dev; set the same
# keys in the Vercel project environment for production. Everything is optional:
# the app runs fully on free, keyless public data without any of these.

# WSDOT Traveler Information API access code (free). When set, /api/wa-alerts
# pulls Washington HighwayAlerts for the Walla Walla / US-12 corridor and the
# Walla Walla leg reflects WSDOT closures. When unset, the app degrades to the
# honest "Washington roads not included yet" note. The code is read server-side
# only and never reaches the browser. Request one at:
#   https://wsdot.wa.gov/traffic/api/
WSDOT_ACCESS_CODE=
